  "prompt": "What kind of mobile phones are the best for elderly people?",
  "response": "When choosing a mobile phone for elderly people, consider these features:\n\n1. Simple, user-friendly smartphones:\n- iPhone SE (easy interface, large icons)\n- Doro phones (designed specifically for seniors)\n- Google Pixel with simplified mode\n\n2. Basic phones with large buttons:\n- Nokia 3310 3G\n- Jitterbug Flip\n- Great Call phones\n\nKey features to look for:\n- Large, clear display\n- Big, easy-to-press buttons\n- Hearing aid compatibility\n- Simple menu navigation\n- Emergency call features\n- Long battery life\n- Volume control\n- Hearing aid compatibility\n- Simplified interface\n- SOS/emergency button\n\nSome popular options:\n1. Samsung Galaxy A series (larger screen, simple mode)\n2. Doro 8050\n3. Jitterbug Smart3\n4. Nokia 225\n5. Apple iPhone with accessibility features\n\nConsiderations:\n- Individual tech comfort level\n- Specific needs (vision, hearing, mobility)\n- Budget\n- Preferred features\n\nThe best phone depends on the individual senior's specific requirements and technological familiarity.",
